                    <span>The book has some good ideas -- but they are incomplete. If you want The Rest of the Story you will need to pay Freeman for his services. Example: Freeman says he has a list of over a thousand character traits for creating characters. If he has such a list, it wasn't included with the book. The pages in the book are beautiful; it is a well-crafted book -- just like a fancy brochure. Caveat emptor.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Very Disappointing!!!</div>
                    <div>
